---
layout: landing-layout.njk
title: ""
description: "HomeStart — early access. A calm planner for first-time buyers: cash-to-close, savings, affordability. Not a lender. Join the waitlist."
---

{% from "icons-features.njk" import icon %}

<header class="site-header" id="site-header" data-header>
  <div class="header-inner">
    {% include "brand-logo.njk" %}
    <nav aria-label="Primary">
      <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="#showcase">Preview</a></li>
        <li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="#waitlist" class="nav-cta">Early access</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="main">
  <section class="hero-shell" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
    <div class="section hero">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <p class="hero-badge"><span class="hero-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> Early access · iOS app in development</p>
          <h1 id="hero-heading">Plan your first home with room to breathe.</h1>
          <p class="hero-sub">See the full cash picture—not just a down payment. Track savings, stress-test affordability, and follow a guided roadmap. Built for first-time buyers—not a lender or listing marketplace.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn btn--primary" href="#waitlist">Get early access</a>
            <a class="btn btn--secondary" href="#showcase">See the preview</a>
          </div>
          <p class="hero-note">We’ll email you when HomeStart hits the App Store—launch updates only, no spam.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="showcase" id="showcase">
          <div class="showcase__device">
            <figure class="app-showcase" data-app-preview>
              <div class="mock-frame mock-frame--premium">
                <div class="mock-screen mock-screen--photo" role="tabpanel" id="app-preview-panel" aria-labelledby="app-preview-tab-plan">
                  <img
                    class="app-preview-img"
                    src="/images/preview-plan.jpg"
                    alt="HomeStart plan overview: target home, closing-cash progress, estimated payment, and savings summary. Sample data."
                    width="471"
                    height="1024"
                    decoding="async"
                    fetchpriority="high"
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="preview-tabs" role="tablist" aria-label="Switch app preview screen">
                <button type="button" class="preview-tab" role="tab" id="app-preview-tab-plan" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="app-preview-panel" data-preview-src="/images/preview-plan.jpg" data-preview-alt="HomeStart plan overview: target home, closing-cash progress, estimated payment, and savings summary. Sample data.">Plan</button>
                <button type="button" class="preview-tab" role="tab" id="app-preview-tab-numbers" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="app-preview-panel" data-preview-src="/images/preview-numbers.jpg" data-preview-alt="HomeStart numbers view: readiness score and savings, cash-to-close, and payment comfort. Sample data.">Numbers</button>
                <button type="button" class="preview-tab" role="tab" id="app-preview-tab-accounts" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="app-preview-panel" data-preview-src="/images/preview-accounts.jpg" data-preview-alt="HomeStart accounts view: linked home fund, progress toward goal, and cash breakdown by purpose. Sample data.">Accounts</button>
              </div>
            </figure>
          </div>
          <p class="showcase__caption">Real in-app screens (sample data). We’re still polishing details before App Store launch.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--trust" id="trust" aria-labelledby="trust-heading">
    <h2 id="trust-heading" class="visually-hidden">Trust and product boundaries</h2>
    <ul class="trust-grid" role="list">
      <li class="trust-pill">
        <span class="trust-pill__label">Planning only</span>
        <span class="trust-pill__text">Illustrative numbers—your lender sets real terms.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="trust-pill">
        <span class="trust-pill__label">Your choice</span>
        <span class="trust-pill__text">Optional bank linking or manual balances.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="trust-pill">
        <span class="trust-pill__label">Privacy-minded</span>
        <span class="trust-pill__text">Connect only what you want. <a href="/security-overview/">Security overview</a></span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--features" id="features" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
    <header class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">Inside the app</p>
      <h2 id="features-heading">Built around how buying actually works</h2>
      <p class="section-intro section-intro--narrow">Four jobs that matter before you ever talk to a loan officer—plus a path that keeps you oriented.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="features-grid">
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("cash") }}</div>
        <h3>Full cash to close</h3>
        <p>Down payment plus closing, reserves, and move-in costs—one target, so you’re not surprised at the wire.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("savings") }}</div>
        <h3>Savings you can track</h3>
        <p>Watch progress against that total as you save month to month—honest math, no fantasy shortcuts.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("afford") }}</div>
        <h3>Affordability, in context</h3>
        <p>Place a future payment next to rent, income, and debts—so “comfortable” means something concrete.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon-wrap feature-icon-wrap--accent" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("link") }}</div>
        <h3>Link banks—or skip them</h3>
        <p>Optional connections (e.g. via Plaid) to refresh balances. Prefer not to? Enter amounts yourself.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="feature-card feature-card--wide">
        <div class="feature-icon-wrap" aria-hidden="true">{{ icon("roadmap") }}</div>
        <h3>A roadmap, not a maze</h3>
        <p>Step-by-step milestones and short lessons so you always know the next right thing—especially when everything feels new.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--cta-mid" aria-labelledby="cta-mid-heading">
    <div class="cta-mid">
      <div class="cta-mid__copy">
        <h2 id="cta-mid-heading">Be first when we ship</h2>
        <p>HomeStart is in active development. Waitlist members get App Store launch news—nothing else.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="#waitlist">Join the waitlist</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--how" id="how-it-works" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
    <header class="section-header">
      <p class="section-label">How it works</p>
      <h2 id="how-heading">Start small. Refine as you learn.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <h3>Ground it in your numbers</h3>
        <p>Income, rent, debts, and savings on hand.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <h3>Define a working target</h3>
        <p>Price or monthly comfort—then taxes, insurance, timing.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <h3>Keep pace over time</h3>
        <p>Update savings, optionally link accounts, follow the roadmap.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--waitlist" id="waitlist" aria-labelledby="waitlist-heading">
    <div class="waitlist waitlist--premium">
      <p class="waitlist__badge">App Store · coming soon</p>
      <h2 id="waitlist-heading">Get on the list</h2>
      <p class="waitlist__lead">Early access to download when we launch. One inbox: launch and product milestones—not marketing drips.</p>
      <ul class="waitlist__bullets" role="list">
        <li>Notify me at App Store release</li>
        <li>Occasional progress updates as we ship</li>
        <li>Unsubscribe anytime</li>
      </ul>
      <form class="waitlist-form waitlist-form--premium" id="waitlist-form" novalidate>
        <div class="field-wrap">
          <label class="visually-hidden" for="waitlist-email">Email address</label>
          <input type="email" id="waitlist-email" name="email" autocomplete="email" placeholder="Email address" required inputmode="email">
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary btn--submit btn--lg" id="waitlist-submit">Request access</button>
      </form>
      <p class="waitlist__fineprint">We use your email only for waitlist and launch-related messages. See our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
      <div class="waitlist-status" id="waitlist-status" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <span class="footer-brand">{{ site.name }}</span>
    <ul class="footer-links">
      <li><a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy</a></li>
      <li><a href="/terms-of-service/">Terms</a></li>
      <li><a href="/security-overview/">Security</a></li>
      <li><a href="mailto:{{ site.supportEmail }}">Contact</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="footer-meta">© {{ site.copyrightYear }} {{ site.companyLegalName }}</p>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
  (function () {
    var h = document.getElementById("site-header");
    if (!h) return;
    function tick() {
      h.classList.toggle("is-scrolled", window.scrollY > 8);
    }
    tick();
    window.addEventListener("scroll", tick, { passive: true });
  })();
</script>
